# CODEOWNERS — auto-routes PR reviews to track owners
#
# Syntax: <path-pattern>  <@user1> [<@user2> ...]
# Last matching pattern wins (most specific patterns last).
# Reference: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositories-settings-and-security/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Team handles:
#   @6ummy           — 정우   (PM / all-tracks, persona voice gatekeeper)
#   @limserenahansol — 한솔   (Frontend + LLM)
#   @yunchai-build   — 윤채   (LLM + Infra)
#   @genius-chang    — 예슬   (Quant)
#   @jlee0810        — 준원   (Infra + Quant)  ← joined 2026-05-19
#
# Status: ACTIVE — repo is public, branch protection on `main` requires
# CODEOWNERS approval. Anyone (including external contributors via fork)
# must get an approval from the listed owner(s) before merge.
#
# Outside contributors: open a PR from your fork. The owner for the changed
# paths will be auto-requested as reviewer. See CONTRIBUTING.md §2.

# ─── Defaults: 정우 sees every PR (PM / all-tracks role) ───────────────
*                                       @6ummy

